    "A New and Concise Bible Dictionary": "This is a type of Christ's kingdom as established on earth, when presents, as willing tribute, will be sent from all nations to the Lord Jesus `[char_Jesus_Ref]`. Ps. 45: 12; Ps. 72: 10, 15; Isa. 60: 9.\n25. Some of the mountains are 2,000 to 3,500 feet high, but from the west they look much higher because of the depression of the Jordan valley. Pasturage abounds in Gilead, and accounts for Gad and the others choosing it for their cattle. The `[group_Canaanites_Gen_10]` district is divided into north and south by the river Jabbok ( Zerka ). The `[group_Canaanites_Gen_10]` northern part is cultivated and has numerous villages; but the southern is mostly held by nomadic tribes, with but little cultivation, and having but one inhabited town now, called es Salt, . In the days of Ahab Ramoth-gilead was in possession of the Syrians, which was followed by all Gilead and Moab falling into their hands. 1 Kings 22: 3; 2 Kings 10: 32,\n25. The `[group_Canaanites_Gen_10]` balm of Gilead was proverbial for its healing virtues. Jer. 8: 22; Jer. 46:"
